The possibility recount the ballots in Michoacán individually is considered
According to the information from Prep the difference between the first and second place in the election of the governor is nearly 27 percent, with 879 votes have not been counted out of a total of 6074.
The possibility of Einzelauszählung of ballots in this year's elections in Michoacán a reality, because under the Programa de Resultados Electorales Preliminares (Prep) data issued the difference between the first and second place in the elections nearly 27 percent, with 879 votes have not been counted out of a total of 6074.
In this sense, the President of the Consejo General del Instituto Electoral de Michoacán (IEM), María Ángeles de has rid Llanderal Zaragoza, recalls that the election body had just last November 9, adopted a set of rules on the harmonisation of local rules with the reforms of the federal states in election affairs.
It should be remembered that neither Michoacán had adjusted its political constitution nor his electoral law nor its law on the election of justice to the reforms adopted by Congress, so that they were not emerged from this round of elections. The governor, Leonel Godoy Rangel avoided their publication in the State Gazette within the deadline with the argument to have objections.
On November 9, the Supreme Court of Mexico ruled (SCJN) on the local legislature's constitutional complaint and did the voice of the state representative on the constitutional reforms as "invalid and illegal" because it does not have the right to "decide or veto against it."
María Ángeles de release Llanderal said in an interview on the possibility of Einzelauszählung of votes that the possibility thanks to the adoption of the directives by the Consejo General del IEM now that the local electoral authority could recount the ballots in part or in full.
So the packages contained one or more electoral votes under the following conditions can partly be counted The results in the protocols do not agree; the protocol on the count and -berechnung received files moderately or not, it is not in possession of the chairman of the electoral commission or there are obvious errors or modifications in the protocols.
Moreover, the total count of completely full ballot papers can be done if there is a difference between the presumed winner and who is in the second place, which is equal to or less than one percent, provided at the start of the sitting an explicit request of party-or coalition chairmen have, which is the second of these candidates.
The count can also occur in their entirety, if it is established after the conclusion of the proper calculation that the difference between the presumed winner and the candidate in second place is the same, or less than one percent, provided there is an explicit request by a representative of the party, whose candidate has become second, and in this case, the election packages, which were suspended a partial count would be excluded.
It is worth noting that the elections are in Morelia in the same situation, where the difference between the first and second place is under Prep just 0.16 percent, while the votes of a total of 129 923 election protocols have not been counted yet.
